Example Usage

# Extract data from the development server
dev_data <- extract_workzone_table(
  table_name = "example_table",
  server_key = "dev_server",
  config_file = "config/config.yaml"
)

# Extract data from the production server
prod_data <- extract_workzone_table(
  table_name = "example_table",
  server_key = "prod_server",
  config_file = "config/config.yaml"
)

Explanation for Juniors

	1.	Flexibility:
	•	The function can handle multiple servers by simply switching the server_key parameter.
	•	All server-specific details are stored in the YAML file, keeping the function clean and reusable.
	2.	Avoid Duplication:
	•	Instead of maintaining separate functions for different servers, a single function handles both cases, improving maintainability.
	3.	Scalability:
	•	Adding new servers or making changes to existing ones requires only updating the YAML file, not the code.
	4.	Security:
	•	Sensitive credentials like uid and pwd are fetched from environment variables, ensuring they are not hardcoded.

